<subSubSection id="A831C8F627A74F33BD60377A02DDD79D" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph id="3C9602969F1291F36E3F4E72680F1C57" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="76EE85F33B27F0F3535DEACBDF12CB34" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. Records of 
<taxonomicName id="E9D44A52DDB3C01CD6DE552A7C7C0F77" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphaerosyllis brevicirra" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevicirra">Sphaerosyllis brevicirra</taxonomicName>
from the Western Mediterranean by 
<bibRefCitation id="C1E98A8454C51E13125B0727751BFC26" author="Alos, C" journalOrPublisher="Cahiers de Biologie Marine" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="329 - 339" title="Adiciones a la fauna de anelidos poliquetos de la peninsula Iberica: familia Syllidae" volume="30" year="1989">
<normalizedToken id="E558844799A089E4EA12A8D7578B1FEB" originalValue="Alós">Alos</normalizedToken>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
and from the Aegean Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="A5D46C14946A10E2C21AB7827E2B434B" author="Simboura, Nomiki" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. National and Kapodistrian University of Athens, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Θαλάσσοι μακροβενθικοί Πολύxαιτοι (AnnelidaPolychaeta) της Ελλάδας: Συστηματική, Οικολογία, Ζωογεωγραφία" year="1996">Simboura 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5F2088DFD1135DE444B4F76835270E62" author="Cinar, Melih Ertan" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Ege University, Izmir" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Tuerkiye'nin Ege Denizi sahillerinde dagilim goesteren Syllidae (Polychaeta-Annelida) tuerlerinin taksonomisi ve ekolojisi" year="1999">
<normalizedToken id="64A929B0416750C3D4B226470319B4C7" originalValue="Çınar">Cinar</normalizedToken>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
) belong to an undescribed 
<taxonomicName id="2477F92B523C07B03D32979F9A93FB04" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Prosphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prosphaerosyllis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Prosphaerosyllis</taxonomicName>
species (
<bibRefCitation id="3DB17464E8E11768CA7FBA12FE652296" author="San Martin, G." journalOrPublisher="Fauna Iberica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination=": 544 pp" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos MA, et al. (Eds)" volume="21, Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CA, SAIC, Madrid" year="2003">
San 
<normalizedToken id="BE586EEF1E1624694E51387406D242E7" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="AFBE3D0CAF9113E80A654012C10D1BFF" author="Faulwetter, Sarah" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="281 - 326" title="An account of the taxonomy and distribution of Syllidae (Annelida, Polychaetes) in the eastern Mediterranean, with notes on the genus Prosphaerosyllis San Martin, 1984 in the Mediterranean" volume="150" year="2011">Faulwetter et al. (2011a)</bibRefCitation>
examined the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="3B5D87DB8CC06B01610439B246FA5267" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Prosphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevicirra">Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra</taxonomicName>
from the Red Sea and found that the species bears a conspicuous papilla on each dorsal cirrus. All descriptions and illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="F4962FCF4F0732BE1BFF3B77DAAA90CD" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Prosphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevicirra">Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra</taxonomicName>
from the Mediterranean lack these papillae. In addition, these specimen descriptions differ from 
<taxonomicName id="B9881A9B53CBB9C43E40F7280F9D4405" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Prosphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevicirra">Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra</taxonomicName>
by the absence of dorsal cirri on chaetiger 2 (reported as present by 
<bibRefCitation id="FDF06C4E495509BC22431373F74BB851" author="Alos, C" journalOrPublisher="Cahiers de Biologie Marine" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="329 - 339" title="Adiciones a la fauna de anelidos poliquetos de la peninsula Iberica: familia Syllidae" volume="30" year="1989">
<normalizedToken id="F7ACD694CCF01C8F3E049BF1DF4C06B9" originalValue="Alós">Alos</normalizedToken>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
but in fact absent (
<bibRefCitation id="40964146902904FDF5CC376272A0CE44" author="San Martin, G." journalOrPublisher="Fauna Iberica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination=": 544 pp" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos MA, et al. (Eds)" volume="21, Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CA, SAIC, Madrid" year="2003">
San 
<normalizedToken id="E5E17758B855BCFD74564773A25EEC5C" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
) and by thicker aciculae.
</paragraph>
